txt.en: Anglalaith wishes to make some wreaths to commemorate this Yule season.\n\n<rgb=#FF0000> NOTE: This quest will be removed from your quest log when the current festival ends. </rgb>

'I wish you a Yule to remember, [placeholder]. The festivals to honour the seasons are always my favourite times of the year. Nature goes through such wonderful changes; indeed, the beauty can be quite overwhelming.

'I have a tradition at Yule where I make wreaths from the boughs of the evergreen bushes and present them to the others as a way to honour the winter season. I am nearly halfway done with this year's wreaths, but unfortunately I have run out of branches.

'If you could, head into the hills to the west and retrieve some for me so I can finish making the wreaths. I would be greatly indebted to you.'
The bushes can be found to the west of Duillond.\n\nAnglalaith has asked you to gather some branches from several bushes so that he may finish making his Yule wreaths.
'These branches will do perfectly, [placeholder]. I will sing the songs of Yule while I craft the remainder of the wreaths, and I will add your name in thanks.'
Anglalaith is at Duillond.\n\nAnglalaith will be pleased to receive the branches you gathered and begin work on more wreaths.
'Have you gathered branches for my wreaths, yet? It is not a festival without wreaths.'
'These branches will do perfectly [placeholder]. I will sing the songs of Yule while I craft the next batch of wreaths and I will add your name in thanks.'
